Asked the Minister of Public Administration and Home Affairs : (a) Is he aware that Mrs. Lilani Patabendige of 9/20, Jayawardenapura, Ampura, was appointed as an Acting General Registrar of Marriages for the Wewagampattuwa North Division in the Ampara district on 13.11.2002, and functioned in that post since then ? (d) Will he take action to reppoint Mrs. Lilani Patabendige to the said post ? (e) If not, why ?

Asked the Minister of Housing and Public Amenities,- : (a) Is she aware that the General Manager of the National Housing Development Authority, Mr. Wasantha Wijeratne has obtained two houses from the Raddolugama and Wewagodella Housing Schemes in violation of Section 9 of the Housing Authority Act? (b) Will She admit that, - (i) Houses are sold to married couples and not to single individuals; and, (ii) the above Wewegodella house has been obtained for his unmarried daughter furnishing false fast and documents, claiming that she was married? (c) Will she state,- (i) the number and the date of purchase of the house purchased from the Wewagodella Housing Complex; (ii) whether the date on which the marriage of the daughter was registered and the date on which the house was purchased tally; (iii) the other property purchased from the Authority, their value, extent, the date of purchase and the area from where the purchase was made ? (d) Will she inform this House, the individuals and public establishments who have been offered houses and lands belonging to the Housing Development Authority from the year 2005? (e) Will she take necessary steps to implement formally, paragraph (2), part iv of Section 23 of the Housing Authority Act, No. 17 of 1979 which has been violated by the General Manager concerned ? (f) If not, why?

Asked the Minister of Sports and Public Recreation, : (a) Will he inform this House, - (i) the number of certificates and the number of medals that were needed for each of the National Sports Festivals held from 2000 to 2005 separaely; (ii) the number of certificates and medals that had been purchased for each year from 2000 to 2005; and (iii) the names of the institutes that supplied certificates and medals in respect of each of the years above and the prices offered ? (b) Is he aware that a massive irregularity has occurred in purchasing medals and printing certificates for the National Sports Festivals conducted by the Ministry of Sports from 2000 to 2005 ? (c) Will he state in this House, - (i) whether the formal tender procedure has been followed in procuring certificates/medals; (ii) if so, the names, the addresses and the designations fo the members of the Tender Board concerned ? (d) Will he State (i) the persons, responsible for the irregularity which has occurred; and , (ii) the measures that have been taken against them ? (e) If not why ?

asked the Minister of Education, : (a) Is he aware that, (i) Mr. A. Yogarajah, office peon attached to the National School, Paddiruppu in Batticaloa District was promoted to Class II with effect from 01.05.1994 by letter No. Gen. 8/2/04/4/1 and dated 13.11.1996 of the Secretary to the Ministry of Education, North-East Provincial Council ; (ii) several requests made by him to get his promotion to Class I was unduly delayed : (iii) he was absorbed to the Central Government as Paddiruppu Central College was made to a National School ; (iv) his contemporaries are still working in the Provincial Counil and were promoted after ten years of service from their date of promotion to Class II ? (b) Will he take suitable action to grant his promotion to Class I without further delay, as he is frustrated in his service ? (c) If not, why ?
( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) Hon. Minister, can you kindly tell me a little about this in English? . .
( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha) Yes. .
( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) If you say that he will get his promotion. I will not raise this matter. . .
( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha) Hon. Kanagasabai, he was employee of the North - East Provincial Council earlier. Later this school had been promoted to a National School. .

( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha) Earlier he was a Government Servant of the North-East Province under the Provincial Public Service Commission. They have a scheme of promotion. But at that time, under the Line Ministry there was no scheme of promotion So, now we have prepared a scheme of promotion. It has been referred to the Ministry of Public Administration and Home Affairs and we are waiting for their approval and after that this person also can get his due promotion. .

( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) Hon. Minister, it is no fault of his. When he was working in the Provincial Council this school was made a National School. The employees of the Provincial Council are getting the promotion in time. This poor person is going retire in another three months time.

( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha ) That is also only in the North-East Province. In other provinces, they do not have such minutes. . ( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) So, what do you suggest? How can I help this person? How can you help him? . .

( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha) Now, we have done the needful. We have prepared a promotion scheme for minor employees, not only for the employees attached to the Line Ministry, but also for other provinces. Now we are waiting for the approval of the Ministry of Public Administration and Home Affairs and we will implement it so that they can get their promotions automatically. . ( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) Kindly expedite it and let this poor man get his promotion before he retires because he is going to retire in another three months time. . .
( . . ) (The Hon. A. D. Susil Premajayantha) No, do not worry. Before that we will do it. . ( . ) (The Hon. T. Kanagsabai) Thank you.
